        <h1>Macular Hole Treatment</h1>
        
        <div style="margin: 40px 0;">
            <h2 style="color: #333; margin-bottom: 20px;">Understanding Macular Holes</h2>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">A macular hole is a small break in the macula, the part of your retina responsible for detailed, central vision. This condition can significantly affect your ability to read, drive, and recognize faces. Early diagnosis and treatment are crucial for the best possible outcome.</p>

            <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 20px 0;">
                <h3 style="color: #8b0000; margin-bottom: 15px;">Warning Signs</h3>
                <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                        <i class="fas fa-circle" style="color: #8b0000; font-size: 8px;"></i>
                        <span>Distorted or wavy central vision</span>
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                        <i class="fas fa-circle" style="color: #8b0000; font-size: 8px;"></i>
                        <span>Difficulty reading or seeing fine detail</span>
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                        <i class="fas fa-circle" style="color: #8b0000; font-size: 8px;"></i>
                        <span>A dark or grey spot in central vision</span>
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                        <i class="fas fa-circle" style="color: #8b0000; font-size: 8px;"></i>
                        <span>Straight lines appearing bent or distorted</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin: 40px 0;">
            <h2 style="color: #333; margin-bottom: 20px;">Stages of Macular Holes</h2>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 20px;">
                <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #8b0000; margin-bottom: 15px;">Stage 1: Foveal Detachment</h3>
                    <p>Early stage where the macula begins to separate from the underlying tissue. Early intervention at this stage often leads to better outcomes.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #8b0000; margin-bottom: 15px;">Stage 2: Partial-Thickness Hole</h3>
                    <p>A partial break develops in the macula, causing increased vision distortion and potential central vision loss.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #8b0000; margin-bottom: 15px;">Stage 3-4: Full-Thickness Hole</h3>
                    <p>A complete break through the macula develops, significantly affecting central vision. Prompt surgical intervention is typically necessary.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin: 40px 0;">
            <h2 style="color: #333; margin-bottom: 20px;">Treatment Options</h2>
            <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px;">
                <h3 style="color: #8b0000; margin-bottom: 15px;">Vitrectomy Surgery</h3>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">The main treatment for a macular hole is vitrectomy surgery. This procedure involves:</p>
                <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 15px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                        <i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="color: #8b0000;"></i>
                        <span>Removal of the vitreous gel from the eye</span>
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 15px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                        <i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="color: #8b0000;"></i>
                        <span>Careful peeling of any membranes that may be causing traction</span>
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 15px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                        <i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="color: #8b0000;"></i>
                        <span>Insertion of a gas bubble to help the hole close</span>
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 15px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                        <i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="color: #8b0000;"></i>
                        <span>Post-operative face-down positioning for optimal results</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin: 40px 0;">
            <h2 style="color: #333; margin-bottom: 20px;">Recovery Process</h2>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Recovery from macular hole surgery typically involves:</p>
            <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 15px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                    <i class="fas fa-clock" style="color: #8b0000;"></i>
                    <span>Face-down positioning for several days to 2 weeks</span>
                </li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 15px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                    <i class="fas fa-calendar-alt" style="color: #8b0000;"></i>
                    <span>Regular follow-up appointments to monitor healing</span>
                </li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 15px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                    <i class="fas fa-eye" style="color: #8b0000;"></i>
                    <span>Gradual vision improvement over several months</span>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

